design.md                       # AR-003: Shared types/constants design\n├── delta-spec.md                   # Root delta spec\n├── test_spec.md                    # Test specification\n├── .sdd_prompt.md                  # SDD prompt\n├── coverage.out                    # Test coverage output\n│\n├── pkg/                            # Go packages\n│   ├── apis/\n│   │   └── runtime/\n│   │       └── v1alpha1/           # CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n│   └── workloadmanager/            # HTTP API handlers + lifecycle management\n│       ├── handler/                # Sandbox CRUD handlers\n│       └── response/               # HTTP response utilities\n│\n├── client-go/                      # Generated Kubernetes client code\n│   ├── clientset/                  # Typed clientset\n│   ├── informers/externalversions/ # Shared informer factory\n│   └── listers/runtime/v1alpha1/   # Listers for CRDs\n│\n├── changes/                        # Change proposals (AR-001 through AR-007)\n│   ├── AR-001/ through AR-006/     # Completed changes (design.md, proposal.md, delta-spec.md, tasks.md)\n│   └── AR-007/                     # PENDING: K8s Reconciler controller (design.md is TODO template)\n│\n├── sandbox-orchestration/          # Core sandbox orchestration design + spec\n├── session-routing/                # Session-aware routing design\n├── session-store/                  # Redis/Valkey session store design\n├── idle-cleanup/                   # Agentd idle cleanup controller design\n├── code-execution/                 # PicoD code execution design\n├── cli-toolkit/                    # CLI tool design\n├── python-sdk/                     # Python SDK design\n├── ci-cd/                          # CI/CD pipeline design\n├── deployment/                     # Deployment design\n├── integrations/                   # Integration design\n│\n├── testing/                        # TDD manifest\n└── coverage.out\n```\n\n**Note:** There is NO `cmd/` directory in the current source tree. The project.md mentions binaries under `cmd/` but they do not exist yet.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Contents of `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n\nThe directory has two subpackages:\n\n#### `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/`\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `sandbox_create.go` | `SandboxCreateHandler` -- creates AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter sandboxes via dynamic client, uses informers/listers, waits for reconciler watcher, resolves pod IP, builds entry points |\n| `sandbox_delete.go` | `SandboxDeleteHandler` -- deletes sandboxes by session ID or by name, supports both Sandbox and SandboxClaim GVRs |\n| `sandbox_lifecycle.go` | `LifecycleManager` -- background cleanup loop for expired sandboxes, GetSandboxStatus, ListSandboxes, ExtendSandboxTTL endpoints |\n| `models.go` | Request/response types: `CreateSandboxRequest`, `CreateSandboxResponse`, `SandboxInfo`, `SandboxStatus`, `EntryPoint` |\n| `constants.go` | GVR variables (AgentRuntimeGVR, CodeInterpreterGVR, SandboxGVR, SandboxClaimGVR), kind constants, label/annotation keys, default TTL values |\n| `sandbox_lifecycle_test.go` | Tests for LifecycleManager (696 lines) |\n| `sandbox_delete_test.go` | Tests for SandboxDeleteHandler |\n\n#### `pkg/workloadmanager/response/`\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `response.go` | HTTP response helpers: `JSON()`, `Created()`, `Error()`, `ErrorWithID()` with `SuccessResponse`/`ErrorResponse` wrappers |\n| `response_test.go` | Tests for response helpers |\n\n#### Key Interfaces Defined in handler/\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx, info) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID, info) error\n    GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n    DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID) error\n    ListSandboxes(ctx) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\ntype SandboxReconcilerWatcher interface {\n    WatchSandboxOnce(namespace, name string) (<-chan SandboxStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype TokenCache interface {\n    GetOrCreateUserK8sClient(namespace, saName, token string) (dynamic.Interface, error)\n}\n\ntype UserClientFactory interface {\n    CreateUserClient(token string) (dynamic.Interface, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. API Type Definitions (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n\n**API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n#### AgentRuntime\n```go\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta\n    metav1.ObjectMeta\n    Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec\n    Status AgentRuntimeStatus\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort       `json:\"targetPort,omitempty\"`\n    Template           *SandboxTemplate   `json:\"podTemplate\"`\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration   `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration   `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxTemplate struct {\n    Labels      map[string]string\n    Annotations map[string]string\n    Spec        corev1.PodSpec   // Full K8s PodSpec\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreter\n```go\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta\n    metav1.ObjectMeta\n    Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec\n    Status CodeInterpreterStatus\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort                     `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n    Template           *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate  `json:\"template\"`\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration                 `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration                 `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n    WarmPoolSize       *int32                           `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n    AuthMode           AuthModeType                     `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`  // \"picod\" or \"none\"\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate struct {\n    Labels           map[string]string\n    Annotations      map[string]string\n    RuntimeClassName *string\n    Image            string\n    ImagePullPolicy  corev1.PullPolicy\n    ImagePullSecrets []corev1.LocalObjectReference\n    Environment      []corev1.EnvVar\n    Command          []string\n    Args             []string\n    Resources        corev1.ResourceRequirements\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n    Ready      bool               `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Shared Types\n```go\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    PathPrefix string       `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n    Name       string       `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    Port       uint32       `json:\"port\"`\n    Protocol   ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`  // \"HTTP\" or \"HTTPS\"\n}\n\ntype ProtocolType string   // ProtocolTypeHTTP = \"HTTP\", ProtocolTypeHTTPS = \"HTTPS\"\ntype AuthModeType string   // AuthModePicoD = \"picod\", AuthModeNone = \"none\"\n```\n\n#### Constants\n```go\nconst (\n    AnnotationKeyRuntime = \"agentcube.io/runtime\"\n    AnnotationKeyVersion = \"agentcube.io/version\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing Controller/Reconciler Patterns\n\n#### Pattern A: Handler-based with Watcher (Current, in workloadmanager)\nThe existing `SandboxCreateHandler` uses a `SandboxReconcilerWatcher` interface for one-shot waiting:\n```go\ntype SandboxReconcilerWatcher interface {\n    WatchSandboxOnce(namespace, name string) (<-chan SandboxStatus, error)\n}\n```\nThis is **NOT** a full controller-runtime reconciler -- it is a synchronous wait mechanism where the handler registers a channel, creates the CR, then waits (up to 2 minutes) for the reconciler to signal \"running\" status.\n\n#### Pattern B: controller-runtime Reconciler (agentd idle-cleanup)\nThe `idle-cleanup/design.md` documents a proper controller-runtime reconciler for the `agentd` binary:\n```go\ntype Reconciler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n}\n\nfunc (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\nfunc (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n```\nThis watches `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1 Sandbox` resources and deletes them based on idle timeout annotations. It uses:\n- `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).Complete(r)`\n- `ctrl.Manager` with disabled metrics (`BindAddress: \"0\"`) and health probes\n\n#### Pattern C: Background Lifecycle Manager (current, in workloadmanager)\nThe `LifecycleManager` uses a simple ticker-based cleanup loop (not a K8s reconciler):\n- Runs every `CheckInterval` (default 5 minutes)\n- Lists sandboxes from Store, checks expiry, deletes via dynamic client\n- Start/Stop with mutex-guarded state\n\n#### Pattern D: Planned AR-007 Reconciler (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED)\nThe `changes/AR-007/proposal.md` and `delta-spec.md` define a comprehensive `SandboxReconciler` that:\n- Uses `SharedInformerFactory` + `workqueue.RateLimitingInterface`\n- Watches AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, and Pod resources\n- Maps CR `status.conditions` (Ready) to Store states (pending/running/terminated)\n- Exponential backoff: initial 5s, max 5min, max 15 retries\n- Default 2 worker goroutines\n- Graceful shutdown: stop informer, drain queue (30s timeout), close store\n- Prometheus metrics: reconcile_total, reconcile_duration_seconds, reconcile_errors_total, workqueue_depth, workqueue_adds_total\n- **Status: NOT IMPLEMENTED** -- `design.md` is a TODO template, `tasks.md` is empty\n\n---\n\n### 5. Key Dependencies (from go.mod)\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | K8s API types (corev1, etc.) |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | K8s meta types, runtime, errors |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | K8s client (dynamic, typed, informers, workqueue) |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.22.2 | Controller-runtime framework (scheme builder, manager) |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP framework for workload manager |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | UUID generation for session IDs |\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | v1.11.1 | Testing framework (assert, require, mock) |\n| Go version | 1.25.0 | Language version |\n\nNotable indirect dependencies:\n- `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` (referenced in design docs but not in current go.mod -- may be part of a larger go.mod not shown)\n- `k8s.io/kube-openapi`, `gopkg.in/evanphx/json-patch.v4`, `go.yaml.in/yaml/v2`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Client-Go Generated Code Structure\n\n```\nclient-go/\n├── clientset/\n│   ├── clientset.go          # Interface: RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n│   ├── fake.go               # Fake clientset for testing\n│   └── typed/runtime/v1alpha1/  # Typed clients for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter\n├── informers/externalversions/\n│   ├── factory.go            # SharedInformerFactory interface with Start/Shutdown/WaitForCacheSync/Runtime()\n│   └── runtime/              # Informers for runtime API group\n└── listers/runtime/v1alpha1/\n    └── expansion_generated.go  # Lister interfaces for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter\n```\n\nThe informer factory is a thin wrapper that can delegate to a real `k8s.io/client-go/informers.SharedInformerFactory`:\n```go\ntype SharedInformerFactory interface {\n    Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n    Shutdown()\n    WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[string]bool\n    Runtime() runtime.Interface\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. Relevant Configuration and Manifest Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `go.mod` | Module definition, all dependencies |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package`, `+groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go` | GroupVersion, SchemeBuilder, AddToScheme, Kind constants |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Auto-generated DeepCopy methods for all types |\n| `testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` | TDD requirements: T/C ratio > 0.4, line coverage >= 80% |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` | Full specification with Given/When/Then scenarios |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/design.md` | Detailed design documenting all packages and behaviors |\n| `changes/AR-007/` | The pending reconciler change (proposal + delta-spec are complete, design.md is empty TODO) |\n\n---\n\n### 8. Key Observations\n\n1. **No `cmd/` directory exists** -- The project.md mentions `cmd/` for binaries but none are present in the source tree. The sandbox-orchestration design.md documents what `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` and `cmd/agentd/main.go` should look like.\n\n2. **AR-007 (K8s Reconciler) is the critical missing piece** -- The proposal and delta-spec are fully written but the actual implementation (`design.md`, `tasks.md`, and all reconciler code) does not exist yet. This is the change that will add the `SandboxReconciler` to `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/`.\n\n3. **Two sandbox CRD types consumed but not owned** -- AgentCube creates `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1 Sandbox` and `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1 SandboxClaim` resources (from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`), but these are external CRDs. AgentCube owns only `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs.\n\n4. **Testing conventions** -- Tests use `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert/require`, `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake` for fake dynamic clients, `gin.CreateTestContext` with `httptest.NewRecorder` for HTTP handler testing, and mock Store interfaces.\n\n5. **Response format** -- All handlers wrap responses in `response.SuccessResponse{Data: ...}` or `response.ErrorResponse{Error, Code, RequestID}`.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_288d84401ffeT4iOCLLbfwSje6","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775820585979,"end":1775820789667}}}}
